The paper focuses on privacy risks and data leakage effects in mobile computing, which are closely related to the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses methods and recommendations for limiting privacy leakages, which falls under the category of systems and information retrieval (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper touches on the social and ethical implications of mobile computing, which could be classified under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses ongoing research in the field, which could be classified under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
